    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-02-05T13:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-02-05T13:36:00-05:00" n="375"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d375">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 818.00/72</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Hale</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">San José</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-05T13:00:00-05:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 5, 1917—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I sent ex-President González and Castro Quesada to Limon by special train in
                    charge of John M. Keith, special agent of the Legation, and clerk Smith. They
                    were safely delivered to the <hi rend="italic">Metapan</hi> which sailed last
                    night at 9.30.</p>
                <p>Ex-President González asked me to ask the United States Government not to
                    recognize Tinoco. I suppose he means if Tinoco should be elected President as a
                    result of his call for a constitutional assembly.</p>
                <p>There is absolute quiet and all affairs proceed as before the <hi rend="italic"
                        >coup d’état</hi>. It has almost ceased to be discussed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hale</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
